jdbc stands for java database connectivity. It is an API which is used to connect with the data base.
import java.sql.*; // is a package in which there is interface-> statement interface,connection interface,driver interface,prepared statement,result set etc.
Before jdbc, we use odbc. But problem is that they are written in C. ANd platform dependent. +less secure. 

5 steps of databse connectivity->
Register the drivers.
create connection
create statement
execute query. (we execute query with help of statement)
close con.


Prepared Statement is the sub interface of statement interface. It is used to execute a parametrized query. For ex-> sql="Select --- where name=?";
                                                                             
